HEADWORD: Cabbling
<hw>Cab"bling</hw> <pr>(-bl⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Metal.)</fld> <def>The process of breaking up the flat masses into
which wrought iron is first hammered, in order that the pieces may be
reheated and wrought into bar iron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

